# .cursorrules - iOS Exclusive React Native App
- This is an iOS-exclusive React Native project using Expo
- Use TypeScript for all files
- Use NativeWind for styling (Tailwind CSS for React Native)
- Use Zustand for state management
- Use React Query for server state management
- Follow iOS-specific React Native best practices and performance guidelines
- Use functional components with hooks
- Prefer const assertions and proper typing
- Keep components in src/components/ directory
- Keep screens in src/screens/ directory  
- Keep stores in src/stores/ directory
- Keep API calls in src/api/ directory
- Use absolute imports with path mapping
- Follow iOS Human Interface Guidelines (HIG)
- Handle safe areas properly with react-native-safe-area-context
- Use React Navigation for navigation
- Implement proper loading states and error boundaries
- Optimize specifically for iOS platform
- Use iOS-specific Expo modules and APIs
- Follow iOS app store guidelines and requirements
- Use iOS-native UI patterns and components
- Implement proper iOS haptics and animations
- Handle iOS-specific lifecycle events
- Use iOS-specific storage and security features
- Structure files: exported component, hooks, helpers, types
- Make everything modular - each feature should be self-contained
- Create a new branch for every feature, bug fix, or significant change
- Keep features isolated and avoid cross-feature dependencies
- Don't overengineer solutions - keep it simple
- Test specifically on iOS devices and simulators
- Use iOS-specific testing frameworks when needed
- Follow iOS accessibility guidelines (VoiceOver, etc.)
- Implement iOS-specific push notifications
- Use iOS-specific navigation patterns (tab bars, navigation controllers)
- Handle iOS-specific permissions and privacy 